article.headline: Northeastern 58, Hofstra 51
article.story: BOSTON -- Quincy Ford and Jonathan Lee each scored 17 points to lead Northeastern to a 58-51 win over Hofstra on Saturday. The game was close in the first half until the Huskies (11-10, 7-4 Colonial Athletic Association) took control after halftime, surging to a 40-29 lead with 16:11 to play in the game on a jumper by Lee -- who went 7 of 9 from the floor. Ford made one of his four 3-pointers with 6:21 left to give Northeastern its largest lead at 12 points. Reggie Spencer finished with 13 points and a team-high eight rebounds for Northeastern, which has won two in a row. Hofstra (7-16, 1-10) -- which played its fifth game in 11 days -- struggled against the Huskies' 2/3 zone defense, shooting 29.6 percent (16-54) from the floor. Mike Moore led the Pride with 17 points, and David Imes had 10 points and eight rebounds.
